# Agent Coach project conventions

Agent Coach ships meta-skills for auditing agent-facing instruction prose. Judgement-heavy by design; see README.md for scope.

## Where content lives

- **Runtime artefacts:** `skills/<skill>/SKILL.md`, `skills/<skill>/references/*`. Deployed when a consumer copies a skill to `~/.cursor/skills/`.
- **Author-only sidecar:** `skills/<skill>/MAINTENANCE.md`. Sync constraints; not loaded at runtime.
- **Companion (Cursor):** `rules/<skill-name>.mdc`. Description-activated authoring discipline.
- **Companion (Claude Code):** `skills/<skill-name>-rule/SKILL.md`. Same content; adapted frontmatter.

## Writing discipline

- Self-apply the `tighten-instructions` rubric on any agent-facing prose you edit.
- Conservative default: protect dated incident notes, binary safety invariants, brief role framing, tone calibration, and per-level tool descriptions.
- Repo-agnostic and portable in shipped skills.
- Imperative, dense, concrete. No preambles.

## Toolkit discipline

- New skills only when a pattern recurs across enough independent files; otherwise add a rubric category to an existing skill.
- No mechanisation (CLI/lint companions).
- Never write into `~/.cursor/skills/` or other consumer locations from this workspace.

## Naming

- **Agent Coach** in prose; **`agent-coach`** for paths.
